Job Title: Senior Corporate Analyst | Big 4 Second Mover
Ad Text:
High profile Infrastructure giant is amid large-scale transformation. This is a highly complex business and its operations span across Australia. 

The Transformation Director is seeking a high-performing Senior Corporate Analyst to support the execution of a complex, multi-year transition. This role will play a key part in supporting the development of a strategic partnership, with a focus on, capital program, project execution, transition planning, and stakeholder alignment.

This is a 6-month contract to permanent opportunity. 

Key duties include:

Support execution of a complex, multi-year strategic partnership, contributing to operational readiness, diligence, and transition planning activities.
Operate within a PMO environment, tracking progress, managing dependencies, and supporting issue/risk escalation and resolution.
Prepare executive-ready materials, dashboards, and analysis to support senior stakeholder communication and governance forums.
Coordinate cross-functional workstreams and external advisors to ensure timely alignment of milestones, deliverables, and decision points.
Support procurement and capital planning analysis on ad hoc basis
Exposure and opportunity to add input to commercial terms considering transitional service considerations, and value preservation opportunities
Key criteria to be considered:

CA/CPA/CFA qualified ideally 
Big 4 Second mover with exposure to transformations, M&A, or FP&A within complex environment. 
Sector experience in infrastructure, industrials or other capital-intensive industries
Exceptional communication and stakeholder management

Overview of the Role

We are seeking an experienced Senior Power BI Developer to design, build, and optimise enterprise-grade analytics and reporting solutions for complex client environments. You will work closely with data engineers, product teams, and senior stakeholders to translate business questions into clear, high-impact insights.

This role is hands-on and delivery-focused, suited to someone who enjoys owning analytics outcomes end-to-end, from data modelling through to executive-ready dashboards.

Australian work rights are required for this position.

Key Responsibilities

Design and develop scalable Power BI dashboards and reports for enterprise and regulated environments
Model complex datasets using star schemas and best-practice semantic layer design
Build and optimise DAX measures with a strong focus on performance and maintainability
Partner with data engineers to shape data pipelines and ensure reporting-ready data models
Work directly with stakeholders to define KPIs, reporting requirements, and analytical outcomes
Implement row-level security and governance controls aligned to data security standards
Drive consistency, quality, and usability across reporting solutions
Contribute to analytics standards, patterns, and best practices across engagements

Skills and Experience

Required:

Strong commercial experience delivering Power BI solutions in production environments
Advanced Power BI development skills including DAX, Power Query (M), and data modelling
Experience working with SQL-based data platforms (e.g. SQL Server, Azure SQL, Snowflake, Synapse)
Proven ability to translate complex business requirements into clear, actionable insights
Experience working in agile, delivery-focused teams
Strong communication skills and confidence engaging with senior stakeholders

Preferred:

Experience in financial services, insurance, or other regulated industries
Exposure to Azure data services (ADF, Synapse, Fabric)
Experience designing analytics for large-scale or multi-tenant platforms
Understanding of data governance, security, and access control patterns
Experience working alongside AI, ML, or advanced analytics teams

This is a unique opportunity to shape the future of our analytics and data capability through high-impact Power BI solutions. The successful candidate will be both a strategic thinker and a hands-on practitioner, capable of delivering trusted insights that drive financial, operational, and decision-making outcomes at scale.
